wikipedia_page.main: Robert Frost (born 1793 at North Elmham, Norfolk; date of death unknown) was an English first-class cricketer associated with Norfolk who was active in the 1830s. He is recorded in one match, totalling 13 runs with a highest score of 10.

response: Robert Frost (1874–1963) was an American poet.

*Robert Frost (pioneer), one of the dead in the Fort Parker massacre
